Dexmedetomidine has been known to protect the lung against inflammation and oxidative stress in diverse clinical settings.

 The investigators aimed to investigate the lung protective effect of dexmedetomidine in patients undergoing thoracic aortic surgery with hypothermic circulatory arrest, which is associated with systemic inflammatory response, and oxidative stress.

